.remind

The idea is to have a very simple syntax where you will be able to filter tasks.

Example:

```
(state eq todo and tags contains wodo) or remind eq true
```

I have a project in golang called [Quang](https://github.com/marcos-venicius/quang).
Is it possible to use golang inside C? I mean, bind it somehow?
Because if we can, I'm thinking about using this library and just update the library if it needs to.
If it's not possible to use it (not just possible, to be fair, if it's to hack-ish), we are going
to implement a new query lang library in C ourselfs.

And, if I need to implement a new query lang library, I'm gonna do it a header only library, so it's easy to
use it wherever we want, and of course, the first use will be the wodo project.

